Jack Ma is a Chinese business magnate, investor, and philanthropist. He is the co-founder and former executive chairman of Alibaba Group, a multinational technology company. Born in 1964 in Hangzhou, China, Ma founded Alibaba in 1999. Under his leadership, the company became one of the world's largest e-commerce businesses, with operations in more than 200 countries. Ma has also been actively involved in philanthropy and education, and has been recognized for his contributions to the business world and to society. In 2019, he announced that he would step down as Alibaba's executive chairman and concentrate on philanthropy and education.
